description: Me and Mr. SlimBones paying tribute to  'The Owl and the pussy-Cat' by Edward Lear 1871 "The Owl and the Pussycat went to sea in a beautiful per green boat, They took some honey and plenty of money, Wrapped up in a five pound note. The Owl looked up to the stars above, and sang to a small guitar, "o lovely Pussy! O Pussy, my love, What a beautiful Pussy you are, You are, you are! What a beautiful pussy you are!"
